Make a graph

  1. Tell R we are using ‘ggplot’
  2. Tell R what data we are using and what variables we want to plot
  3. What type of graph we are creating
ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_point()

1. Create a column graph with this data 2. Create an area graph with this data

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_col()

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_area()

### Intro to customizing ‘ggplot’ graphs

  • color=(update point or line colors) -fill = (update the fill characteristic of an element)
  • linetype -pch = (value) -size -alpha
ggplot(data=ci_np, aes(x=year, y=visitors)) + geom_line(color="coral", linetype="dashed")

ggplot(data=ci_np, aes(x=year, y=visitors)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue",
             size = 4,
             alpha = 0.5)

ggplot(data=ci_np, aes(x=year, y=visitors)) +
  geom_point(color = "coral",
             size = 3,
             alpha = 1)
